place.name: FREISTHORPE
place.gazetteerText: FRIESTHORPE, a parish in the district and county of Lincoln; 1 mile W by S of Wickenby r. station, and 5 SSW of Market-Rasen. Post town, Market-Rasen. Acres, 586. Real property, £840. Pop., 46. Houses, 10. The property is divided between two. The living is a rectory, united with the rectory of Snarford, in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £340.* Patron, alternately the Bishop of Lincoln and the Dean and Chapter of Lincoln. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
